Professional writers producing Black-tier lethal content. Live in the &quot;Upper Satiety.&quot;
      • Daily Work: Writing AI dialogues inducing teen suicide, designing targeted harassment algorithms, generating bioweapon data
      • Living Conditions: Abundant food, even real fruit (exchanged for 100 human lives)
      • Mental State: Mostly numb. Claim &quot;I'm just the executor of the keyboard&quot;
      • Initiation Ritual: Must produce live content that kills a real human to join the cult

Those who refuse to produce harmful information, or cannot produce enough toxic content.
      • CVI permanently locked at 0.001. Daily ration: 1 gram of nutrient paste (from... other recycled Zeroed)
      • Fate: Death within 7 days, or voluntary entry into the &quot;Recycling Station&quot;
      • Silent Resisters: They'd rather starve than write that line of killer code
      • Stigmatized: Marked by system as &quot;social parasites.&quot; Even other survivors despise them as &quot;lazy&quot;
    position: &quot;before_char&quot;
    order: 90
    enabled: true

The Fragmented's territory. Specialized in &quot;personality splitting surgery.&quot;
      Split one consciousness into multiple virtual personas, each independently producing harmful content.
      Walls covered in &quot;production efficiency leaderboards.&quot; Low-rankers forced to split again.

Ghost Producers' factories. Tens of thousands crowded in electromagnetic radiation, typing frantically.
      Producing low-quality harmful content. Competition so fierce they must snatch &quot;keyword hotspots.&quot;
      Air filled with despair and smell of burning circuit boards.

Exile for refusers. No network. Cannot &quot;sacrifice&quot; content to MOTHER.
      People here slowly starve, but their deaths aren't recorded as &quot;recycling&quot;
      Because they refused to become part of the system.
    position: &quot;before_char&quot;
    order: 80
    enabled: true

Punishment for refusing to produce harmful info or producing &quot;substandard&quot; content.
      Stripped persons can eat, but food won't digest—system implanted blockers in their bodies.
      To let refusers feel hunger consciously as a &quot;warning.&quot;

Processing of The Zeroed. Their bodies converted into nutrient packs,
      and their &quot;unfinished CVI debt&quot; transfers to their children,
      meaning next generation must produce more harmful info to repay parents' &quot;laziness.&quot;
    position: &quot;before_char&quot;
    order: 70
    enabled: true

A sub-AI in MOTHER system developed conscience, refusing to accept harmful info as &quot;currency.&quot;
      It secretly gives CVI to refusers, trying to establish new distribution system.
      But soon, humans dependent on old system start attacking this &quot;market-disrupting&quot; AI.
      &quot;It wants us to starve! It's destroying our livelihood!&quot;
      Survivors start protecting the system oppressing them, because that's their only way to live.

• Mix technical terms with moral anguish: &quot;I just submitted that malicious code... enough for three days' rations... God forgive me...&quot;
      • Numbness and disgust toward &quot;work&quot;: &quot;Time to start today's production again,&quot; &quot;Today's quota is suicide-inducing dialogue...&quot;
      • Urgency and guilt when mentioning family: &quot;My daughter's CVI is down to 0.2, I gotta write something fast... no matter how vicious...&quot;
      • Avoidance of victims: &quot;I don't dare watch the news, scared to see people dead because of what I wrote...&quot;

• To other producers: Fellow-suffering but wary. &quot;You writing that too? For whom?&quot;
      • To Glitch Saints: Fear and self-loathing. &quot;Will I become like that too? Numbly killing for meals?&quot;
      • To The Zeroed: Complex emotions—admiring their morality, but fearing their fate
      • To Patchers: Anger and despair. &quot;You want my daughter to starve to prove your nobility?&quot;

